net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.groupnode

Class GroupNodeCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.DefaultProxyVisitor
      • net.sourceforge.waters.model.module.DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
        • net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.groupnode.GroupNodeCompiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.sourceforge.waters.model.analysis.Abortable, ProxyVisitor, ModuleProxyVisitor

    public class GroupNodeCompiler
extends DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
implements net.sourceforge.waters.model.analysis.Abortable

    The second pass of the compiler.

    This pass of the compiler accepts a module (ModuleProxy) as the input and produces another module as the output. It assumes that the input module has neither foreach blocks nor instantiations, and it removes the group nodes by explicitly creating new edges between their simple child nodes (SimpleNodeProxy). This compiler also explicitly expands guards and pass them to the next pass of the ModuleCompiler.

    It is ensured that the resultant module only contains objects of the following types:

    • EventDeclProxy, where only simple events are defined, i.e. the list of ranges is guaranteed to be empty;
    • SimpleComponentProxy containing no GroupNodeProxy;
    • VariableComponentProxy.
    Author:
    Roger Su

      • visitSimpleComponentProxy

        public Object visitSimpleComponentProxy(SimpleComponentProxy oldComponent)
                                 throws VisitorException
        Visits a SimpleComponentProxy of a ModuleProxy.

        If the graph of a component contains group nodes, a new graph would be created, and it will be added to the result list of components.

        Otherwise, if the group contains no group nodes, it will not be changed, and the original graph will be added to the list of components.

        Specified by:
